e at one entrance of the channel and a small tissue on the other), incubate for 15~min. Take images of 5-10 different fields of view containing at least 100 cells in total with the same imaging parameters as the main experiment. <\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#84CE84","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":961852,"guid":"0F3580E0AF5F11EAB06D17958C722BAE","previous_id":961854,"previous_guid":"236D2C60AF6011EAB06D17958C722BAE","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"93D4EBB02A07445D80D634E0FBC905B9","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"pH sensor calibration"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"C4E3FD65F072464CAB137F9CDEFA306D","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Plot the calibration curve as a ratio of emission intensities for excitation at 395 nm and 475 nm against pH.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span>Fit with the sigmoid function R<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">395\/475<\/span><span>=(a<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">1<\/span><span> e<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;\">k(pH-pH<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;vertical-align:super;\">0<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;vertical-align:super;\">)<\/span><span>+a<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">2<\/span><span>)\/(e<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;\">k(pH-pH<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;vertical-align:super;\">0<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;vertical-align:super;\">)<\/span><span>+1), where a<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">1<\/span><span>, a<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">2<\/span><span>, k and pH<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">0<\/span><span> are free fitting parameters.<\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Use the calibration curve to rec